msgid ""
"Bombs can always be attached to Bridge Repair Huts, but the resulting "
"explosion will not destroy the bridge unless \\ "
":tag:`IvanBomb.DestroysBridges=yes` is set."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/weapons/ivanbombs.rst:87
msgid "Bomb Overlay Image"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/weapons/ivanbombs.rst:89
msgid ""
"A bomb overlay image file has to contain zero or more blocks (each "
"consisting of two frames) of flickering images for time bombs, followed "
"by a single, optional frame used as image for Death Bombs."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/weapons/ivanbombs.rst:93
msgid ""
"The image file used for only Death Bombs thus might contain a single "
"frame only, while the image file used only for time bombs are allowed to "
"contain the flickering image blocks only and omit the last frame. If a "
"bomb might be both, the image file has to contain images for both bomb "
"types."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/weapons/ivanbombs.rst:102
msgid ""
"The original :file:`bombcurs.shp` contains thirteen frames: six blocks of"
" flickering images at the beginning, followed by one image at the end for"
" the Death Bomb that was planned but cut from :game:`Red Alert 2`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/weapons/ivanbombs.rst:106
msgid ""
"Death Bombs will always display their only frame while for time bombs the"
" animation defined by the flickering image blocks is stretched to play "
"over the entire lifetime of the bomb defined by :tag:`IvanBomb.Delay`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/weapons/ivanbombs.rst:113
msgid ":tagdef:`[Weapon]IvanBomb.Image=filename, *excluding*the .shp extension`"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/weapons/ivanbombs.rst:111
msgid ""
"The SHP file for the image to display over a unit that has a bomb "
"attached to them, in the format \"filename\"(the \".shp\" extension is "
"automatically added by the engine). If the image cannot be loaded then "
"the game will fall back to the default :file:`bombcurs.shp`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/weapons/ivanbombs.rst:128
msgid ":tagdef:`[Weapon]IvanBomb.FlickerRate=integer`"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/weapons/ivanbombs.rst:116
msgid ""
"The number of frames at which the bomb image will alternate between the "
"two flickering images in a block to give the impression of a flickering "
"fuse. If :value:`0`, flickering is disabled. Defaults to "
":tag:`[CombatDamage]IvanIconFlickerRate`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/weapons/ivanbombs.rst:121
msgid ""
":tag:`IvanBomb.FlickerRate=5` means the first frame is shown 5 frames, "
"then the second one for 5 frames, then the first one again for 5 more "
"frames, ...."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/weapons/ivanbombs.rst:124
msgid ""
"If flickering is disabled, all images in all blocks are played over the "
"lifetime of the bomb. The second frame of each block is not ignored and "
"it thus is not necessary to add an empty frame to fill up a block. Still,"
" the logic only deals in full flickering image blocks and will ignore the"
" last frame if the number of frames in the file is odd."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/weapons/ivanbombs.rst:130
msgid ""
"The logic works best if :tag:`IvanBomb.Delay` is a multiple of the number"
" of flickering image blocks and :tag:`IvanBomb.FlickerRate`. Then each "
"frame is played smoothly for the same amount of time."
msgstr ""

